  <title>13.4.1 Signal Control Timing Chart</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading4">Signal Control Timing Chart</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The input/output signals are controlled by signal control when the signal set is not assigned to any group (1 ~ 4) or when the signal set is the only one assigned to a group.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Single signal control is described below with an example case in which USDO1/USDI1 are controlled with M580 and M581.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">USDO1 is turned on by M581 and USDO1 is turned off by M580. All other input/outputs signal sets are controlled in the same manner with different M codes.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The timing chart below shows the operation with the following functions:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
